{{Refimprove|date=January 2015}} {{Use dmy dates|date=December 2010}} {{Infobox flag | Name = Groningen | Article = | Image = Flag of Groningen.svg | Alt = | Noborder = <!-- Leave blank for rectangular flag; for non-rectangular flag, type "no". --> | Nickname = Flag of Groningen | Morenicks = | Use = Provincial flag | Symbol = <!-- |Use="6-digit FIAV usage code" is required. --> | Proportion = 2:3 | Adoption = 17 February 1950 | Design = | Designer = [[Jan Tuin]] }}
The '''[[flag]] of [[Groningen (province)|Groningen]]''' is an official symbol of the province. The flag was approved 17 February 1950,<ref>{{nl icon}} [http://www.provinciegroningen.nl/servicelinks-provincie-groningen/over-de-provincie/provincievlag/ Provincievlag], [[Groningen (province)#Government|Province of Groningen]]. Retrieved on 3 February 2014.</ref> and is based upon the flag of the town of [[Groningen (city)|Groningen]] and the coat of arms of the region [[Ommelanden]]. The colours red, white and blue are derived from the [[coat of arms]] of the Ommelanden, and the white and green are shown in the Groningen town flag. The colours of the town are in the centre of the flag to represent the central location of Groningen town, which is the capital of the province.
==Design== The ratio of the flag is 2:3, the same as the [[Flag of the Netherlands|Dutch flag]]. The white cross has the width of 1/3 of the height of the flag and the green cross 1/9 of the flag height. The colors are defined as the Pantone-colors 032U (red), 300U (blue) and 355U (green).
==History== In the year 1913 Van der Laars did a proposal to use a flag for the province of Groningen. His proposal was a flag that was based upon the flag of the Ommelanden. The blue stripe in the middle was altered to the green of the flag from the [[Groningen (city)|city of Groningen]]. He also did two other proposals where he used the colors of the [[coat-of-arms]] of the province of Groningen.
{| |[[File:Flag Ommelanden.svg|thumb|100px|The flag of the Ommelanden]] |[[File:Flag of Groningen City.svg|thumb|100px|The flag of the city of Groningen]] |[[File:Groningenvlagvoorstel 1.svg|thumb|100px|Proposal 1]] |[[File:Groningenvlagvoorstel 2.svg|thumb|100px|Proposal 2]] |[[File:Groningenvlagvoorstel 3.svg|thumb|100px|Proposal 3]] |}
The design of the current flag was made by [[Jan Tuin]], member of the Gedeputeerde Staten of the [[Groningen (province)|province of Groningen]] and later mayor of the [[Groningen (city)|city of Groningen]]. They couldn't agree upon which flag would become the flag of the province. [[Jan Tuin]] proposed to design a new flag, this design was accepted. On 17 February 1950 it was decided by Gedeputeerde Staten that this would become the flag of the [[Groningen (province)|province of Groningen]]. Six days later the ruling was officially published.
